cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the translation of LTL formulas into automata using logical methods.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with automata and their properties.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with the translation of a logical language (LTL) into automata, which can be seen as a programming language.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with automata and their properties, which can be relevant to some areas of machine learning.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the construction of automata, which can be seen as a data structure.
